# Mission_Design

## 1. Applies when
There are quests, main-line missions, side missions, random encounters, notice-board
tasks, faction commissions, or personal requests.

## 2. This document owns
Main missions; side missions; event body text; random encounters; mission choices
and consequences; trigger conditions; rewards; failure states; notice-board tasks;
personal requests.

## 3. This document does NOT own
Map paths; POI density; world map structure; full performance dialogue; gameplay
base numbers.

## 4. Recommended chapter structure
1. Document role · 2. Mission classification · 3. Main missions ·
4. Side missions · 5. Open-world events · 6. Camp personal requests ·
7. Upgrade / boundary rules · 8. TODO

## 5. Common boundaries
- Mission vs World — what happens / choices / consequences vs where and density.
- Mission vs Script — table/structure version vs narrative-performance version.
- Mission vs Readme / Pipeline — content authority vs delivery rules.

## 6. Common audit rules
- Mission body must not flow back into World_Design (WORLD-NO-EVENT-BODY check).
- Cross-reference Mission events to their World mount rules, not rewrite them.
